1. Setting Up the Files:

Create a folder for your project and create three files inside:
index.html (HTML structure for the to-do list)
style.css (CSS styling for the webpage)
script.js (JavaScript code for interactivity)

2. Building the HTML Structure (index.html):

A heading "To-Do List"
A container (div) to hold the to-do list elements.
An input field (input) to enter new tasks.
A button (button) to add tasks.
An unordered list (ul) to display the to-do items.

3. Styling the Webpage (style.css):

4. Adding JavaScript Functionality (script.js):

Select the necessary HTML elements using getElementById.
Attaches a click event listener to the "Add Task" button.
When clicked, it retrieves the task value from the input field.
It checks if the task value is not empty.
